TZ=America/Chicago

# HOST CPU ACCURACY NOTE
#
# Dockhand's collection-worker (Go binary) does not have access to the host
# /proc filesystem (no `- /:/host:ro` volume), so it cannot accurately report
# host CPU utilization. The `cpu` field it sends reflects container-level
# cgroup stats, NOT the full host CPU — expect values much lower than actual.
#
# Compare: beszel-agent has `- /:/host:ro` and reports accurate host metrics.
#
# If Dockhand ever adds a host-proc volume or fixes the collection-worker,
# verify the subprocess-manager CPU formula:
#   File: /app/build/server/chunks/subprocess-manager-JT2DwB2e.js
#   Look for: E(e.envId,e.cpu,e.memPercent
#   The Go worker sends both `cpu` and `cpuCount`; dividing may or may not
#   be correct depending on what unit `cpu` is reported in.
